02/01/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police seized 205kg of heroin found in two trucks in the eastern province of Agri on Tuesday (December 30th), local media reported. Drug-fighting units stopped the trucks at a border gate after they entered the country from neighbouring Iran. They found the heroin in secret compartments. Police arrested the two drivers, both Macedonian nationals. 
In other news Tuesday, Bulgaria's customs service said its officers seized 8kg of heroin at the Kapitan Andreevo checkpoint at the border with Turkey. The drugs were in a truck with Turkish plates headed for the United Kingdom, which crossed the border Monday night. Police detained the Turkish driver and a woman with Bulgarian citizenship who was allegedly hiding the heroin in her bag. (Anadolu news agency, NTV, Xinhua, BTA, Darik - 30/12/08)
